A Kwara State High Court sitting in Ilorin and presided over by Justice Abiodun Adebara has fixed January 15, 2020, for hearing on a suit filed by Asa Investments Limited on the disputed land on which the late Second Republic Senate Leader, Dr. Olusola Sarakai’s Ile Arugbo (Old People’s Home) was built. Governor AbdulRahman AbdulRazaq, House of Assembly, Attorney-General, Director-General, Kwara Bureau of Lands and the Inspector-General of Police, are defendants in the suit. The court, also upon a motion ex-parte and the supporting affidavit dated and filed on January 2, 2020, and after listening to the claimant’s counsel, Mr. A.A. Ibrahim, restrained the defendants and anyone acting on their behalf from further demolishing or further destroying the alleged property of the claimant. To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .